WEBVTT

00:07.870 --> 00:10.180
( <i>bell ringing )</i>

00:12.410 --> 00:14.950
( <i>whistle blowing )</i>

00:29.660 --> 00:31.660
( <i>playing the blues )</i>

00:31.730 --> 00:33.430
Captioning made possible by
20th TV

00:35.030 --> 00:35.570
D-oh!

00:35.630 --> 00:37.040
( screams )

00:51.900 --> 00:53.330
Bart.

00:53.400 --> 00:54.840
Bart!

00:54.900 --> 00:56.070
Hey, Bart.

00:56.140 --> 00:57.570
( <i>snorting )</i>

00:57.640 --> 00:59.210
( <i>gasping for air )</i>

00:59.270 --> 01:00.780
Lisa! It's 6:00 a.m.

01:00.840 --> 01:02.440
Something's wrong.

01:02.510 --> 01:03.780
Dad died.

01:03.840 --> 01:06.000
No, no, he's fine.

01:06.080 --> 01:07.450
What do you know?

01:07.510 --> 01:08.440
I'm relieved.

01:08.510 --> 01:10.240
Bart, my birthday's in two days.

01:10.320 --> 01:11.950
I'm gonna be eight years old.

01:12.020 --> 01:13.020
It's a big number--

01:13.090 --> 01:14.260
almost double digits.

01:14.320 --> 01:15.690
Enjoy it while you can.

01:15.750 --> 01:18.250
Everything changes
when you hit the big 1-0.

01:18.320 --> 01:19.420
Your legs
start to go.

01:19.490 --> 01:21.160
Candy doesn't taste
as good anymore..

01:21.230 --> 01:22.930
Will you please let me pour my
little heart out?

01:23.000 --> 01:24.430
Sorry.

01:24.500 --> 01:26.670
This old-timer does
ramble on sometimes, don't he?

01:26.730 --> 01:29.670
I do so much for you
and yet you have disappointed me

01:29.740 --> 01:31.310
on every one of my birthdays.
Okay.

01:31.370 --> 01:33.140
I've made things for you...

01:33.210 --> 01:34.510
Okay, okay, okay!

01:34.570 --> 01:35.600
It's done.
I'm doing it!

01:35.670 --> 01:37.500
Birthday gift
coming your way!

01:37.580 --> 01:39.250
Oh, thank you.

01:39.310 --> 01:40.980
Bart, watch Maggie
while I get the laundry.

01:41.050 --> 01:41.950
Can do.

01:43.020 --> 01:44.720
Hmm, Krusty Hotline.

01:48.520 --> 01:49.720
<i>Hi, kids!</i>

01:49.790 --> 01:51.890
<i>You've reached
the Krusty Hotline.</i>

01:51.960 --> 01:54.560
<i>If you haven't asked
your parents' permission--</i>

01:54.630 --> 01:55.900
<i>Naughty, naughty</i>

01:55.960 --> 01:57.570
<i>but Krusty forgives you.</i>

01:57.630 --> 01:59.570
<i>Two dollars
for the first minute</i>

01:59.630 --> 02:00.500
<i>50 cents
for each additional minute.</i>

02:00.570 --> 02:02.840
( <i>Krusty laughing hysterically)</i>

02:06.070 --> 02:11.380
( <i>laughter continues )</i>

02:14.180 --> 02:15.220
<i>Thanks for calling, kids.</i>

02:15.280 --> 02:16.850
A new message every day.

02:16.920 --> 02:18.050
Maggie!

02:18.120 --> 02:21.020
Bart, I asked you
to watch your sister.

02:21.090 --> 02:23.630
I tried to stop her,
but she overpowered me.

02:23.690 --> 02:25.890
Who stole my shirt?
Who stole my shirt?!

02:25.960 --> 02:26.960
I washed it.

02:27.030 --> 02:28.160
Thank you, Marge.

02:28.230 --> 02:28.800
Ahh!

02:28.860 --> 02:29.860
Pink?!

02:29.930 --> 02:31.800
I can't wear
a pink shirt to work.

02:31.860 --> 02:33.320
Everybody wears white shirts.

02:33.400 --> 02:35.770
I'm not popular enough
to be different.

02:35.830 --> 02:37.600
Now Homer, don't panic,
you have plenty
of white shirts.

02:37.670 --> 02:39.110
Oh, gimme, gimme, gimme.

02:39.170 --> 02:40.810
Oh, no! Pink!

02:40.870 --> 02:43.070
Pink! <i>Pink!</i>

02:43.140 --> 02:45.750
( <i>sobbing: )
It's all over, Marge!</i>

02:45.810 --> 02:47.350
It's all over!

02:47.410 --> 02:49.340
I don't know how this
could've happened.

02:49.420 --> 02:51.020
Ah, my lucky red hat.

02:51.080 --> 02:52.610
Clean as a whistle.

02:52.690 --> 02:54.890
<i>You! You did this to me!</i>

02:54.950 --> 02:56.680
I... apologize.

02:56.760 --> 02:58.130
Oh please, no ones going
to notice

02:58.190 --> 03:00.130
if you wear
a pink shirt to work.

03:01.530 --> 03:03.630
Mr. Burns:
Wait a minute.

03:03.700 --> 03:05.370
Go back.

03:05.430 --> 03:06.970
Zoom in.

03:07.030 --> 03:09.290
Why is that man
in pink?!

03:09.370 --> 03:11.910
That's Homer Simpson, sir--
He's one of your boob's
from Sector 7-G.

03:11.970 --> 03:14.080
Simpson, eh?
Judging by his
outlandish attire

03:14.140 --> 03:17.080
he's some sort
of free-thinking anarchist.

03:17.140 --> 03:18.740
I'll call security, sir.

03:18.810 --> 03:20.010
Excellent.

03:20.080 --> 03:21.580
Yes, these color monitors

03:21.650 --> 03:23.720
have already paid
for themselves.

03:23.780 --> 03:26.410
Man:
Pink! I don't get
the statement.

03:27.620 --> 03:28.690
Shh.....

03:28.750 --> 03:29.480
Hey, Homer.

03:29.560 --> 03:30.990
we saved you a donut.

03:31.060 --> 03:32.960
It has <i>pink frosting.</i>

03:33.030 --> 03:34.100
( <i>laughter )</i>

03:34.160 --> 03:35.430
Thanks.

03:35.490 --> 03:36.620
It looks...

03:36.700 --> 03:38.070
Hey, wait a minute!

03:38.130 --> 03:40.070
Just because I'm wearing
a pink shirt

03:40.130 --> 03:43.400
doesn't mean I'm some kind
of a.. pink donut-eater.

03:43.470 --> 03:45.110
Although it is tempting.

03:45.170 --> 03:46.070
( <i>smacks lips )</i>

03:46.140 --> 03:47.210
Drop that donut.

03:47.270 --> 03:49.600
Let's go, pinky.

03:49.680 --> 03:51.010
You don't understand.

03:51.080 --> 03:54.950
My son just threw his red hat in
with the white laundry.

03:55.010 --> 03:57.640
Spare me the tiresome antics
of the Simpson family.

03:57.720 --> 03:58.950
Take him away.

03:59.020 --> 04:01.820
His body cavity search
revealed nothing.

04:01.890 --> 04:04.190
We must have X-rayed him
a hundred times.

04:04.260 --> 04:06.090
Maybe he's telling the truth.

04:06.160 --> 04:07.530
Or perhaps you two
are in cahoots.

04:07.590 --> 04:09.520
Smithers, I seem to recall
you had a penchant

04:09.600 --> 04:10.800
for bell-bottomed
trousers

04:10.860 --> 04:12.060
back in '79.

04:12.130 --> 04:14.640
That was my costume
for the plant production

04:14.700 --> 04:15.500
of <i>H.M.S. Pinafore.</i>

04:15.570 --> 04:16.870
Yes, of course.

04:16.940 --> 04:19.269
Your spirited hornpipe
stole the show, as I recall.

04:19.339 --> 04:21.040
Now doctor, what should we do

04:21.110 --> 04:22.640
about our
free-wheeling fop
over here?

04:22.710 --> 04:25.280
Well Monte, it used to be that
establishing a patient's sanity

04:25.340 --> 04:26.340
took months.

04:26.410 --> 04:27.150
That's all changed

04:27.210 --> 04:29.140
thanks to the Marvin Monroe

04:29.210 --> 04:31.210
Take-Home Personality Test.

04:31.280 --> 04:33.610
20 simple questions
that will determine

04:33.690 --> 04:37.590
just how crazy
or <i>"meshuggener" someone is.</i>

04:37.660 --> 04:39.090
"Print name."

04:39.160 --> 04:40.860
Oh!

04:42.130 --> 04:44.100
( <i>humming )</i>

04:44.160 --> 04:46.020
Hmm.

04:46.100 --> 04:47.640
Hmm!

04:48.930 --> 04:50.700
Honey, do me a favor.

04:50.770 --> 04:52.210
Fill out this form.

04:52.270 --> 04:54.940
This is an intimate
psychological profile.

04:55.010 --> 04:56.880
I can't fill this out
for you.

04:56.940 --> 04:58.210
All right, all right.

04:58.280 --> 04:59.710
I'll get Lisa to do it.

04:59.780 --> 05:01.620
Lisa, you like homework.

05:01.680 --> 05:03.450
Could you fill out
this form for me?

05:03.520 --> 05:04.690
Well, all right...

05:04.750 --> 05:06.220
if you listen to the
poem I just wrote.

05:06.290 --> 05:07.890
D-ohh..! Okay.

05:07.950 --> 05:11.080
"'Meditations on Turning Eight'
by Lisa Simpson.

05:11.160 --> 05:12.960
"I had a cat named Snowball.

05:13.030 --> 05:14.260
"She died, she died!

05:14.330 --> 05:17.130
"Mom said she was sleeping.

05:17.200 --> 05:19.070
"She lied, she lied!

05:19.130 --> 05:21.300
"Why, oh why, is my cat dead?

05:21.370 --> 05:24.040
"Couldn't that Chrysler
hit me instead?

05:24.100 --> 05:26.060
"I had a hamster named Snuffy.
He died.."

05:26.140 --> 05:27.110
No deal.

05:27.170 --> 05:28.770
Dad, maybe you should do this.

05:28.840 --> 05:30.010
Son, it's no different

05:30.080 --> 05:32.310
than the time
I let you vote for me.

05:32.380 --> 05:34.050
Remember
that absentee ballot?

05:34.110 --> 05:35.240
Oh, yeah.

05:35.310 --> 05:38.480
Our $50,000 home video
finalists are:

05:38.550 --> 05:40.890
<i>"Man Breaking Hip..."</i>

05:40.950 --> 05:41.980
( <i>man screaming )</i>

05:42.050 --> 05:43.720
<i>"Dog on Fire."</i>

05:43.790 --> 05:46.560
<i>Ruff! Anybody order a hot dog?</i>

05:46.630 --> 05:48.860
( <i>laughing )</i>

05:48.930 --> 05:50.470
Look at him!

05:50.530 --> 05:53.030
<i>...and finally,
"Baby with a Nail Gun."</i>

05:53.100 --> 05:53.870
( <i>nail gun fires )</i>

05:53.930 --> 05:55.290
Aw.

05:55.370 --> 05:56.940
<i>It's time to
cast your votes now.</i>

05:57.000 --> 05:57.970
"Dog on Fire!"
"Dog on Fire!"

05:58.040 --> 05:59.470
Hey Dad..Do you hear voices?

05:59.540 --> 06:02.440
Yes I'm hearing one now,
though I'm trying to watch TV.

06:02.510 --> 06:04.350
Yes. Are you quick to anger?

06:04.410 --> 06:06.510
Bart, shut up
or I'll shut you up!

06:06.580 --> 06:08.580
Yes. Do you wet your pants?

06:08.650 --> 06:13.350
Even the best of us
has an occasional accident.

06:13.420 --> 06:14.520
Tsk, tsk, tsk.

06:14.590 --> 06:16.690
So did I pass?

06:16.760 --> 06:18.290
( <i>laughing: )
No.</i>

06:18.360 --> 06:19.360
Bart!

06:19.420 --> 06:20.550
Careful, men.

06:20.630 --> 06:22.430
He wets his pants.

06:22.490 --> 06:23.590
( <i>siren blaring )</i>

06:26.430 --> 06:27.640
Uhh...

06:27.700 --> 06:29.200
The devil with his fly open.

06:29.270 --> 06:30.300
Right.

06:31.340 --> 06:32.110
That's a spill on the floor

06:32.170 --> 06:33.540
with bugs going after it.

06:33.610 --> 06:34.480
They're gonna eat it.

06:34.540 --> 06:36.210
Good.

06:36.280 --> 06:37.180
The boy!

06:37.240 --> 06:38.370
This isn't fair!

06:38.440 --> 06:40.100
How can you tell
who's sane

06:40.180 --> 06:41.480
and who's insane?

06:41.550 --> 06:43.350
We have a very simple method.

06:44.780 --> 06:47.850
Whoever has that stamp
on his hand is insane.

06:47.920 --> 06:50.860
Guard:
<i>Put him in with
the big white guy</i>

06:50.920 --> 06:53.280
<i>who thinks
he's the little black guy.</i>

06:59.460 --> 07:00.760
Who are you?

07:00.830 --> 07:02.560
Hi, I'm Michael Jackson
from The Jacksons.

07:02.630 --> 07:04.860
I'm Homer Simpson
from the Simpsons.

07:08.340 --> 07:09.280
I can't believe
you never heard of me.

07:09.340 --> 07:10.850
I'm a very popular entertainer.

07:10.910 --> 07:13.820
Of course,
I've heard of you.

07:13.880 --> 07:15.580
You'd have to be
living under a rock
not to know--

07:15.650 --> 07:16.750
What'd you say your name was?

07:16.820 --> 07:17.590
Michael Jackson.

07:17.650 --> 07:18.620
Doesn't ring a bell.

07:18.680 --> 07:19.810
Heard of MTV or Motown?

07:19.890 --> 07:20.350
No.

07:20.420 --> 07:20.890
"Beat It"?

07:20.950 --> 07:21.450
You beat it.

07:21.520 --> 07:22.190
"Thriller"?

07:22.250 --> 07:23.180
What was that last one?

07:23.260 --> 07:24.130
"Thriller."
No.

07:24.190 --> 07:25.260
How about this?

07:25.320 --> 07:28.590
♪ Billy Jean is not my lover ♪

07:28.660 --> 07:33.300
♪ She's just a girl
who says that I am the one ♪

07:33.370 --> 07:37.340
♪ But the kid is not my son ♪

07:37.400 --> 07:38.730
♪ Hee-hee-hee. ♪

07:38.800 --> 07:39.930
Wow!

07:40.010 --> 07:41.440
How do do that thing
with your feet ?

07:41.510 --> 07:42.740
The moonwalk?

07:42.810 --> 07:44.010
No, that thing
with your feet!

07:44.080 --> 07:45.810
Here, look.
Just raise your heel a bit.

07:45.880 --> 07:48.580
Put a little pressure
on the ball of your foot.

07:48.650 --> 07:49.720
Uh-huh.

07:49.780 --> 07:50.820
Huh?

07:50.880 --> 07:51.980
D-ohh!

07:52.050 --> 07:53.190
( <i>laughing )</i>

07:53.250 --> 07:55.060
You seem like a nice guy.

07:55.120 --> 07:56.320
Why'd they
put you in here?

07:56.390 --> 07:58.030
'Cause I wore a pink shirt.

07:58.090 --> 07:59.330
I understand.

07:59.390 --> 08:01.130
People thought I was crazy for
the way I dressed.

08:01.190 --> 08:01.950
What did you wear?

08:02.030 --> 08:03.030
One white glove

08:03.100 --> 08:04.470
covered with rhinestones.

08:04.530 --> 08:06.700
( <i>nonsensical blubbering )</i>

08:06.770 --> 08:08.100
♪ ...and Scratchy Show! ♪

08:23.220 --> 08:27.560
( <i>laughing )</i>

08:27.620 --> 08:30.060
Bart, in the split second
before he died

08:30.120 --> 08:32.960
I bet Scratchy appreciated
his birthday present.

08:33.030 --> 08:34.159
Do you see how this relates
to us?

08:34.230 --> 08:36.200
Hey, you want that once-a-year
empty gesture?

08:36.260 --> 08:37.200
You got it, sis.

08:39.200 --> 08:41.799
Homer:
Hey, Michael,
I don't get it.

08:41.870 --> 08:44.340
These guys
seem as normal
as you and me.

08:44.400 --> 08:45.830
Homer, this is Floyd.

08:45.900 --> 08:47.330
He's an idiot savant.

08:47.410 --> 08:49.710
Give him any two numbers
and he can multiply them

08:49.780 --> 08:51.810
in his head
just like that.

08:51.880 --> 08:52.550
Okay. Five times nine.

08:52.610 --> 08:53.380
Forty-five.

08:53.450 --> 08:54.450
Wow!

08:55.580 --> 08:56.950
We call this guy 'The Chief.'

08:57.020 --> 08:59.250
He's been here
since 1968.

08:59.320 --> 09:00.720
Never says a word.
Never moves a muscle.

09:00.790 --> 09:01.560
Hey, Chief.

09:01.620 --> 09:03.290
Hello.

09:03.360 --> 09:06.530
It's about time
somebody reach out to me.

09:06.590 --> 09:09.660
Gee, I got to call my family.

09:11.260 --> 09:14.390
This is embarrassing
calling them from a nut house.

09:14.470 --> 09:15.940
They think I'm a God.

09:16.000 --> 09:17.240
I could call them for you.

09:17.300 --> 09:19.460
Oh, great. And uh,
try to put a good face on this.

09:19.540 --> 09:20.980
Tell them this is
one of those places

09:21.040 --> 09:23.080
where rich women
lose weight.

09:23.140 --> 09:24.450
( <i>ringing )</i>

09:24.510 --> 09:26.350
Joe's Crematorium--
you kill 'em, we grill 'em.

09:26.410 --> 09:27.880
Hello. Who is this?

09:27.950 --> 09:29.780
Bart Simpson.
Who the hell are you?

09:29.850 --> 09:30.990
I'm Michael Jackson.

09:31.050 --> 09:31.850
<i>The Michael Jackson?</i>

09:31.920 --> 09:33.390
No way.

09:33.450 --> 09:35.720
It's true. I'm with your
father in a mental institution.

09:35.790 --> 09:37.330
Uh-huh. And is Elvis with you?

09:37.390 --> 09:38.730
He could be.

09:38.790 --> 09:40.460
- It's a big hospital.
- <i>Aw, come on.</i>

09:40.530 --> 09:42.600
If you're really Michael Jackson

09:42.660 --> 09:45.000
<i>who were your last four
dates for the Grammys?</i>

09:45.060 --> 09:47.290
Brooke Shields, Diana Ross,
Emmanuel Lewis and Bubbles.

09:47.370 --> 09:48.470
Shiver me timbers!

09:48.530 --> 09:50.390
You <i>are Michael Jackson!</i>

09:50.470 --> 09:52.470
Can you stay on the line
while I'll get all
my friends and relatives?

09:52.540 --> 09:53.540
I'm afraid not, Bart.

09:53.610 --> 09:55.610
Your father really needs
your help.

09:55.670 --> 09:58.470
You don't want him
to get a lobotomy, do you?

09:58.540 --> 09:59.900
<i>Hmm... lobotomy.</i>

10:02.850 --> 10:06.020
That's all right, son.

10:06.080 --> 10:09.110
There's probably a downside
I don't see.

10:09.190 --> 10:10.290
Uh-huh.

10:10.360 --> 10:11.630
New Bedlam Asylum.

10:11.690 --> 10:12.560
Loves us.

10:12.620 --> 10:13.680
Needs us.

10:13.760 --> 10:16.160
Fears he may never see us again.
Got it.

10:16.230 --> 10:17.800
Michael Jackson, whoo-hoo!

10:17.860 --> 10:19.120
I love you, man.

10:19.200 --> 10:20.570
Hey, Mom...

10:20.630 --> 10:22.790
Dad's in a mental
institution.

10:22.870 --> 10:24.040
Oh, my God.

10:24.100 --> 10:25.360
Mother
was right.

10:25.440 --> 10:27.810
( <i>Bart hums "Beat It" )</i>

10:27.870 --> 10:29.300
Now Homer,
don't you worry.

10:29.370 --> 10:31.570
Your family will
be here before
you know it.

10:31.640 --> 10:33.570
Forget it pal.
There's only one way out of here
and it ain't pretty.

10:33.650 --> 10:34.620
What's that?

10:34.680 --> 10:36.520
Dating a
nurse.
Ohhh.

10:36.580 --> 10:39.420
I told you kids you were
going to send your father
to the crazy house.

10:39.480 --> 10:40.950
No Mom, you said poor house.

10:41.020 --> 10:41.990
I said crazy house!

10:42.050 --> 10:42.710
Poor house.

10:42.790 --> 10:43.620
Crazy house!

10:43.690 --> 10:44.290
Poor house.

10:44.360 --> 10:45.630
Crazy house!

10:45.690 --> 10:47.190
Man:
Hello, you've reached

10:47.260 --> 10:50.160
the New Bedlam
wrongly-committed hotline.

10:50.230 --> 10:51.830
All our operators
are currently busy.

10:51.900 --> 10:53.230
Please stay on the line.

10:53.300 --> 10:56.200
♪ Crazy ♪

10:56.270 --> 10:58.240
♪ Crazy for feeling... ♪
( <i>sobbing )</i>

10:58.300 --> 10:59.860
( <i>sobbing )</i>

10:59.940 --> 11:01.840
What's wrong, Homer?

11:01.910 --> 11:04.350
This place
is so strange.

11:04.410 --> 11:08.120
Mike, I'm ashamed
to admit it to another guy

11:08.180 --> 11:11.820
but I'm... scared.

11:11.880 --> 11:13.940
We all get scared
once in awhile.

11:14.020 --> 11:16.090
Maybe I can help you.

11:16.150 --> 11:22.150
♪ Homer, the two of us
need look no more ♪

11:22.230 --> 11:27.970
<i>♪ We both found
what we were looking for ♪</i>

11:28.030 --> 11:31.800
♪ With a friend to call my own ♪

11:31.870 --> 11:34.810
♪ I'll never be alone ♪

11:34.870 --> 11:38.140
♪ And you my friend will see ♪

11:38.210 --> 11:42.380
♪ You've got a friend in me. ♪

11:42.450 --> 11:44.250
( <i>mumbling: )
Hot cakes...</i>

11:44.320 --> 11:45.920
Football...

11:45.980 --> 11:47.850
Boobies...

11:47.920 --> 11:50.420
Bubbles,
it's going to be a long night.

11:50.490 --> 11:51.330
Waffles...

11:53.340 --> 11:55.210
Please, feel free to
express yourselves.

11:55.280 --> 12:00.250
In these sessions, we want you
to feel relaxed and uninhibited.

12:00.320 --> 12:02.890
Okay, so I was working
at an insurance company, right?

12:02.950 --> 12:05.590
Youngest V.P. in the history
of the firm.

12:05.650 --> 12:07.280
The job was my life.

12:07.360 --> 12:10.590
Then, one Monday morning, I got
up, I couldn't leave the house.

12:10.660 --> 12:11.330
I just couldn't.

12:11.390 --> 12:12.520
Was the door locked?

12:12.590 --> 12:13.690
No. I just couldn't face
what was out there.

12:13.760 --> 12:14.570
Was it raining?

12:14.630 --> 12:15.600
No, Homer

12:15.660 --> 12:17.990
Dave suffers
from agoraphobia--

12:18.070 --> 12:20.070
a fear of open areas
and crowds.

12:20.140 --> 12:21.810
Please Dave, go on.

12:21.870 --> 12:25.140
Anyway, that day I knew
I just couldn't make
that long drive to work.

12:25.210 --> 12:26.310
Were you out of gas?

12:27.710 --> 12:29.480
( <i>snorts: )
Baby.</i>

12:29.540 --> 12:32.740
I'm sorry, but your husband
suffers from a persecution
complex

12:32.810 --> 12:36.210
extreme paranoia
and bladder hostility.

12:36.280 --> 12:40.080
If you just talk to him
for five minutes without
mentioning our son Bart

12:40.160 --> 12:41.360
you'd see how sane he is.

12:41.420 --> 12:44.150
You mean there really is
a Bart? Good Lord!

12:44.230 --> 12:46.800
Mmm, pancakes.

12:46.860 --> 12:49.130
Doctor:
Oh, Mr. Simpson,
you've got a visitor.

12:49.200 --> 12:49.830
D-ohh!

12:50.370 --> 12:51.940
Marge!

12:52.000 --> 12:53.700
Oh, Homey!

12:59.570 --> 13:01.770
Mr. Simpson, after talking to
your wife

13:01.840 --> 13:04.070
we believe you're no threat
to yourself or others.

13:04.150 --> 13:06.220
That's the most flattering thing
anyone ever said to me.

13:06.280 --> 13:07.990
Could I have it
in writing, please?

13:08.050 --> 13:09.020
Of course.

13:09.080 --> 13:12.010
Homer:
"Not insane."

13:12.090 --> 13:13.090
Hmm.

13:13.150 --> 13:14.680
I'm proud of you, Homer.

13:14.760 --> 13:17.660
Thanks a lot Michael,
you really helped me
get through this.

13:17.730 --> 13:20.200
If you ever find your marbles,
come visit us.

13:20.260 --> 13:22.500
How about today?
I'm only here voluntarily.

13:22.560 --> 13:23.820
You are? Why?

13:23.900 --> 13:25.770
Well back in 1979, I got real
depressed

13:25.830 --> 13:27.500
when my <i>Off the Wall album</i>

13:27.570 --> 13:29.940
just got one lousy
Grammy nomination.

13:30.010 --> 13:32.910
♪ Happy birthday to me ♪

13:32.970 --> 13:36.270
♪ Happy birthday to me ♪

13:36.340 --> 13:40.540
♪ Happy birthday,
( voice breaking )
overlooked middle child ♪

13:40.620 --> 13:44.020
♪ Happy birthday to me. ♪

13:44.090 --> 13:46.490
( <i>crying )</i>

13:46.550 --> 13:48.380
( <i>horn screeching )</i>

13:48.460 --> 13:49.790
( <i>ringing )</i>

13:49.860 --> 13:52.230
Joe's Taxidermy.
You snuff 'em, we stuff 'em.

13:52.290 --> 13:53.990
Boy, when I get home

13:54.060 --> 13:56.830
I'm going to wrap my hands
around your neck...

13:56.900 --> 13:58.840
and smother you
with kisses.

13:58.900 --> 14:01.610
Homer, whatever they got you on,
cut the dose.

14:01.670 --> 14:03.710
Now listen, I'm bringing
Michael Jackson home

14:03.770 --> 14:05.380
to stay with us for a few days.

14:05.440 --> 14:07.910
Isn't that cute?
He's heard of you.

14:07.980 --> 14:11.380
Make sure we have plenty of
cold cuts, and put some
beer on ice...

14:11.450 --> 14:13.780
I'm a vegetarian
and I don't drink.

14:13.850 --> 14:16.350
Are you sure
you're here voluntarily?

14:16.420 --> 14:17.350
Yes.

14:17.420 --> 14:18.560
Please make sure

14:18.620 --> 14:20.620
he doesn't tell anybody
I'm coming.

14:20.690 --> 14:22.860
Yes, Dad, I solemnly swear

14:22.920 --> 14:25.320
I will not tell
another living soul--

14:25.390 --> 14:26.950
No, not even Milhouse.

14:29.800 --> 14:31.800
Huh?

14:31.870 --> 14:33.170
( <i>grunting )</i>

14:33.230 --> 14:33.990
Hello, Milhouse?

14:34.070 --> 14:34.770
Can you keep a secret?

14:34.840 --> 14:35.910
No.

14:35.970 --> 14:37.410
Oh well, who cares?
Michael Jackson

14:37.470 --> 14:38.410
is coming to my house!

14:38.470 --> 14:40.100
Michael Jackson?!

14:40.180 --> 14:41.710
Michael Jackson?!

14:41.780 --> 14:42.980
Michael Jackson?!

14:43.040 --> 14:44.770
Aunt Bella?! Wait a minute.

14:44.850 --> 14:46.820
I got a call on the other line.

14:46.880 --> 14:48.150
Michael Jackson?!

14:48.220 --> 14:49.390
Michael Jackson?!

14:49.450 --> 14:50.650
Michael Jackson?!

14:50.720 --> 14:51.990
Michael Jackson?!

14:52.050 --> 14:53.350
All:
Michael Jackson?!

14:53.420 --> 14:55.260
Michael Jackson?!

14:55.320 --> 14:57.020
Disk jockey:
<i>We've just been handed a
bulletin from</i>

14:57.090 --> 14:58.860
<i>our rock 'n' rumor
department...</i>

14:58.930 --> 15:01.570
Disk Jockey #2:
<i>Michael Jackson,
the thriller himself,</i>

15:01.630 --> 15:04.200
<i>is moonwalking
his way right here to
our very own Springfield.</i>

15:04.270 --> 15:05.370
Disk jockey:
<i>And while we check it out</i>

15:05.430 --> 15:07.660
<i>Why don't you enjoy
a seldom-heard</i>

15:07.740 --> 15:10.570
<i>extra-long version
of "In-A-Gadda-Da-Vida."</i>

15:10.640 --> 15:12.180
Michael Jackson!

15:12.240 --> 15:14.950
Such a thing happens
once in a blue moon.

15:15.010 --> 15:16.810
Do I dare to leave my post?

15:20.880 --> 15:23.390
( <i>helicopter approaching )</i>

15:23.450 --> 15:25.290
<i>Ay, caramba!</i>

15:27.890 --> 15:30.090
Uh, this is
the most exciting thing

15:30.160 --> 15:32.300
to happen to our fair town

15:32.360 --> 15:36.030
since the Dalai Lama visited
in 1952

15:36.100 --> 15:38.940
and so, I hereby declare
that Route 401

15:39.000 --> 15:41.970
currently known
as the Dalai Lama Expressway

15:42.040 --> 15:46.080
will henceforth be known as
the Michael Jackson Expressway.

15:46.140 --> 15:47.910
I think I can see him.

15:47.980 --> 15:50.110
Oh, here he comes. Oh!

15:50.180 --> 15:52.720
( <i>crowd murmuring )</i>

15:52.780 --> 15:56.420
The guy in the pink shirt
is the father of the family

15:56.480 --> 15:59.450
who it turns out,
was just released
from a mental hospital.

15:59.520 --> 16:02.030
Thanks, everybody.
It's great to be sane.

16:02.090 --> 16:03.360
Crowd:
We want Michael!

16:03.420 --> 16:04.890
We want Michael!

16:04.960 --> 16:05.960
We want Michael!

16:06.030 --> 16:06.930
Here he is.

16:07.000 --> 16:08.630
Here's the guy

16:08.700 --> 16:10.300
you want to see!

16:10.370 --> 16:10.930
Aahh!

16:14.700 --> 16:16.430
Huh? Huh?

16:16.500 --> 16:17.770
He's 300 pounds.

16:17.840 --> 16:18.940
He's white.

16:19.010 --> 16:20.940
He's dressed without flair.

16:21.010 --> 16:25.150
( <i>crowd booing )</i>

16:25.210 --> 16:26.540
Mayor:
What the hell made me think

16:26.610 --> 16:29.240
Michael Jackson would even visit
this jerkwater burg?

16:29.320 --> 16:31.290
You owe us
Michael Jackson.

16:31.350 --> 16:35.150
Don't ever show your face
around here again, you tool.

16:37.030 --> 16:40.400
Bart, the entire town
is howling for your blood

16:40.460 --> 16:43.500
and before I join them,
I have one question.

16:43.570 --> 16:45.570
Today is my birthday.

16:45.630 --> 16:48.830
You promised
you'd get me something and...

16:48.900 --> 16:50.960
and I'm afraid to ask.

16:51.040 --> 16:54.080
Maybe you should trust
that instinct and not ask.

16:54.140 --> 16:55.980
I thought so.

16:56.040 --> 16:58.310
Oh, Bart, you...

16:58.380 --> 17:00.980
( <i>crying )</i>

17:01.050 --> 17:03.350
( <i>door slams )</i>

17:03.420 --> 17:05.020
( <i>growling )</i>

17:05.089 --> 17:06.720
Come off!

17:06.790 --> 17:08.329
I'm sane now.

17:10.329 --> 17:12.230
Dear Bart:

17:12.290 --> 17:15.260
I am using the stationery
Mom and Dad gave me

17:15.329 --> 17:16.770
for my <i>birthday</i>

17:16.829 --> 17:20.940
to inform you that we are now
brother and sister in name only.

17:21.000 --> 17:23.369
Perhaps,
if a professional so advises

17:23.440 --> 17:25.280
I will give you a hug

17:25.339 --> 17:27.609
at some far distant
family reunion

17:27.680 --> 17:30.780
but rest assured,
it will be purely for show.

17:30.850 --> 17:32.720
( <i>crying )</i>

17:32.780 --> 17:35.650
Tsk, tsk, tsk.

17:36.820 --> 17:38.520
Hey, Bart.

17:38.590 --> 17:39.990
Hey, <i>you.</i>

17:40.050 --> 17:41.980
Bart, when I was a kid,
I didn't have much money.

17:42.060 --> 17:44.730
So you know what I did
when my sisters' birthdays
rolled around?

17:44.790 --> 17:45.950
Stiffed them?

17:46.030 --> 17:49.170
No. I wrote them a song
to show that I cared.

17:49.230 --> 17:51.670
I can't write a song.
I'm only ten.

17:51.730 --> 17:54.800
Only ten? When I was your age
I had six gold records.

17:54.870 --> 17:58.510
Hey, Looney Tunes, this is
what Michael Jackson looks like.

17:58.570 --> 18:01.270
You look like
a big, fat mental patient.

18:01.340 --> 18:02.570
You'd be amazed how
often I hear that.

18:02.640 --> 18:04.200
Just leave me alone.

18:04.280 --> 18:06.120
Look boy, either Michael Jackson
is some guy working

18:06.180 --> 18:08.390
in a recording studio in L.A.

18:08.450 --> 18:10.620
or he's here with you
willing to work on this song.

18:10.690 --> 18:12.220
It's your choice.

18:12.290 --> 18:13.760
So long.

18:14.690 --> 18:16.290
Wait, wait, Michael!

18:16.360 --> 18:19.800
You go sit at the piano
and I'll boil some coffee.

18:19.860 --> 18:22.670
